SUMMARY

This figure shows a racy kernel that demonstrates the necessity of shared state
abstraction.

FILES

* k.cl

As given in Figure 2.6 as an OpenCL kernel.

INSTRUCTIONS

1. Copy and paste the kernel into the rise4fun GPUVerify web interface.

  k.cl should be used with the OpenCL frontend
  http://rise4fun.com/gpuverify-opencl

We expect a data race error to be reported.
